<HEADLINE> Cargo Ship Docks With Mir Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Progress M-42 cargo ship docked
with the Russian Mir space station Sunday, the Itar-Tass news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The craft with food, water, fuel and equipment docked from the
side the Kvant module at 17:53 GMT.
</P>
<P>
The flight of the Progress M-41 spaceship ended on Saturday. It
separated from Mir at 11:20 GMT and entered the dense layers of
the atmosphere and ceased to exist at 19:51 GMT, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
The Mir crew, including Russians Viktor Afanasyev, Sergei
Avdeyev and French Jean-Paul Haignere, are expected to take a
space walk next Friday to replace equipment on the station's
exterior, Tass reported.  
</P>
</TEXT>
