<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 21 Killed, 11 Injured in Accidents in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-one people were dead and 11
others injured on Sunday in three separate road accidents in
southern Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian security sources said a mini-bus running to Cairo
collided head-on with a truck on the Asyut-Cairo highway, killing
14 people and injuring six others, the country's Middle East News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In a second accident which took place in the governorate of
Menia, 220 kilometers south of Cairo, two speeding cars ran
head-on into each other on a desert road in the east of the
governorate, leaving four people dead and five others injured, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
A speeding car overturned on the Agricultural Road between
Cairo and Alexandria after the driver tried to brake the car to
avoid an obstacle. The driver, his wife and daughter died in the
accident.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents are common in Egypt due to high speeding and
violations of rules and regulations. Statistics show that more
than 6,000 people die in accidents in a year and over 30,000 are
injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
