<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Police Arrest Two Gunmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Police in Tanzanian capital
arrested two men for allegedly injuring people with guns on
Saturday night in a casino.
</P>
<P>
The Dar es Salaam Regional Police Commander Alfred Gewe said
here Sunday that the suspects were arrested while trying to
escape after the incident occurred in the Las Vegas Casino.
</P>
<P>
Gewe said the suspects were involved in a fighting with some
people for a woman. During the confrontation, the suspects opened
fire, which injured one man on the head and the other on the right
 shoulder. The police are still interrogating the two suspects
while the injured have been admitted to a hospital.
</P>
<P>
One suspect was found with a pistol and seven rounds of
ammunition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
