<DOCNO> XIE19990719.0011 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IMF to Implement Economic Monitoring Program in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary Fund
(IMF) is expected to implement an economic monitoring program in
Angola in September this year, which will possibly lead to
financial aid to the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
Jose Pedro de Morais, visiting IMF official in charge of
African affairs, said here Sunday that the financial institution
will soon send a technical delegation to the country to discuss
the implementation of the program.
</P>
<P>
Morais, who arrived here last Friday, said that the IMF may
begin providing financial aid to the war-torn country in the first
half of the next year, if the monitoring program is going on
smoothly and after the experts have made positive assessment on
the country's economic situation.
</P>
<P>
The monitoring program is a pre-condition for Angola to gain
financial aid from the IMF. It stipulates that the institution
has the right to participate in and assess the economic policies
and measures adopted by the Angolan government. Angola had a
similar program in its last fiscal year, but failed to implement
it owing to the renewed civil war.
</P>
<P>
The program also requires that the Angolan government should
strictly control its expenditure, reduce the number of civil
servants, bring down inflation rate and make its accounts
transparent as well as gradually repealing its foreign exchange
control and privatizing its banks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
