<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-18 18:24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns Turkey's Air-raid on Iranian Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Sunday strongly condemned
the attack by Turkish warplanes on Iranian border villages and
termed it as "unexplainable."
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Hamid Reza Asefi said that
several civilians had been killed while some others injured in
the raid by the Turkish warplanes, the Islamic Republic News
Agency (IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
IRNA said that the Turkish warplanes dropped rockets and
bombs on the border posts in Piranshahr and villages around
the city, Iran's northwestern province of West Azerbaijan
bordering Iraq.
</P>
<P>
However, no details about the Turkish attack were available.
</P>
<P>
The attack was "unprovoked and unexplainable," Asefi said,
adding that the Turkish government should shoulder its
consequences.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, some 10,000 Turkish troops supported by
tanks, armored vehicles, helicopters and warplanes, entered
northern Iraq to crack down on the Turkish Kurdish rebels.
</P>
<P>
Some Turkish media have even claimed that the Turkish
Kurdish rebels have military bases on Iranian territory, but
Iran has repeatedly denied the allegation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
