<HEADLINE> Benchmark Sensex Soars to Historic High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Benchmark sensex set a
historic high of 4810.33 points during the week that was marked by
several new records on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) and the
National Stock Exchange (NSE) as investors celebrated the end of
the eight-week long conflict with Pakistan in Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
The boom in stocks, well supported by no-delivery period in
many Scripps, helped the sensex break the previous all-time record
of 4643.31 points on September 12, 1994, reflecting sustained
rally following all-round hectic buying on the back of continued
purchases by Foreign Institutional Investors (FIIS), who
reportedly made single-day-record purchases of 412 crore Indian
rupee.
</P>
<P>
Even the BSE-100 index cleared its all-time high and closed at
the new record peak at 2030.91 points as also the S&AMP;P CNX Nifty
which soared to 1341.10 before closing at its new record peak of
1335.15 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The BSE sensitive index fluctuated in a wide range of 4810.33
and 4463.44 before closing the week at 4639.94 as against last
weekend close of 4362.87, netting a sharp gain of 277.07 points or
6.35 percent.
</P>
<P>
BSE-200 and the Dollex were quoted substantially up at 456.90
and 175.88 at the weekend compared with last weekend close of
431.44 and 165.55 respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
