<HEADLINE> Lioaning Sinks Wanda at China League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Title holder Dalian Wanda sank
further after going down 2-1 in Sunday's road match to the
upcoming young squad of Liaoning Fushun at the first division of
Chinese soccer league, falling down to the 13rd position in the 14-
team league.
</P>
<P>
At the midway of the 22-match season, the four-time reigning
champion has lost six games and tow in a row. Their only win in
the first half of the season was a 3-1 victory over the 10th-
ranked Guangdong Rongri on June 24.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yuning, the striker of China's Olympic squad, open the
score on a straight header with only seven minutes into play and
gave Liaoning a 1-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
But the struggling Wanda tried to level it 1-1 by Wang Tao's
header at the 55th minute, getting the revenge and pull the Wanda
back on the track.
</P>
<P>
But only 15 munites later, Qu Shengqing added the second goal
for the hosts and retained the top spot on the strikers' ranking
with a total of 9 goals.
</P>
<P>
In an unexpected loped-side match, Luneng Taishan humiliated
Qiangdao Hainiu 4-1 after leading the first half 1-0.
</P>
<P>
The league leaders Shanghai Shenhua were drew to a 0-0
scoreless match.
</P>
<P>
In other games played on Sunday, Sichuan Quanxing finally
forced a 1-1 drew with Shenyang; and the same 1-1 were seen in
the draw between Choingqing Longxin and Wuhan Heart K. 
</P>
