<HEADLINE> India Declares Complete Pullout of Pakistan Troops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 18 (Xinhua) -- India declared on Sunday that
Pakistan troops had completely pulled out from Batalik, Kaksar and
Drass sectors of Kashmir but the army maintained that it would not
withdraw its forces from certain key snow-covered heights in
Kargil even during winter.
</P>
<P>
"We are not going to withdraw out forces. We will wait and
watch the situation," an army spokesman told reporters here today.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Indian troops will clear all areas upto the
line of control in Mushkoh valley, the last of the pockets of
intrusion.
</P>
<P>
Indian Defense Minister George Fernandes announced Saturday
that the war in the Kargil area of Kashmir was over as what New
Delhi termed as intruders had withdrew from Indian side of the
line of control (LOC), the de facto border between the two
countries. 
</P>
