<HEADLINE> Beijing Marathon to Be Held in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing International Marathon,
billed as one of top 10 marathons in the world, will see its 19th
edition held on October 8, right one week after the People's
Republic of China has celebrated the 50th anniversary of its
establishment.
</P>
<P>
The race, which was inaugurated in 1981, will start at Tian'
anmen Square and weaves its way through Eternal Peace Street,
Yuetan Park, Diaoyutai Guesthouse before ending in the Olympic
Stadium, the main stadium of the 11th Asian Games in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Shang Xiutang, general secretary of the Chinese Athletics
Association, said: "It's expected that over 20,000 runners will
take part in the race."
</P>
<P>
The deadline for register is August 31. 
</P>
