<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Repatriates Over 1,000 Somali Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia has repatriated a new
batch of Somali refugees to their homeland, a senior official said
Sunday in Jijiga, some 620 km east of Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,200 Somali refugees, who took shelter at the
Hartishek refugee camp in Jijiga Zone, Somali State, were
transported to northern Somali on Saturday, Tsegaye Meheretu of
the Administration of Refugees and returnees Affairs told local
reporters.
</P>
<P>
Each of the repatriated Somalis had been provided with a
nine-month ration, household utensils, plastic sheetings and 210
birr (about 26 U.S. dollars), he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, more than 52,000 Somali refugees
have been repatriated to their country so far.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there are still more than 193,000 Somali refugees at
eight camps in eastern parts of Ethiopia, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
