<HEADLINE> CA Opens Annual Meeting as Most Powerful IT Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW ORLEANS, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The annual national conference
of Computer Associates International (CA), the world's leading
mission-critical software company, kicked off its annual national
conference here on Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Opening the annual meeting, Charles Wang, CA's chairman and chief
executive officer, said that, "With over 3,000 informative
technical sessions and a newly expanded 350,000 square foot World
Resource Center, CA World remains the industry standard for
top-notch education."
</P>
<P>
For the fifth year in a row, the annual session, known as CA World
1999, stages the industry's most informative and dynamic information
technology (IT) event in one of the world's most entertaining and
delectable cities -- New Orleans, CA officials said.
</P>
<P>
The CA meeting will showcase more than 300 exhibitors and offer
thousands of technical sessions and free educational seminars
designed to provide attendees with a better view of the technology
industry.
</P>
<P>
CA World 1999 provides attendants the unique opportunities to
network with more than 25,000 colleagues, delve deeper into the IT
environment with hands-on workshops, and explore 350,000-square-feet
of cutting-edge technology -- otherwise known as the World Resource
Center, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting welcomes more than 25,000 IT professionals from
around the world to experience succulent food, good fun, and
memorable festivities in New Orleans.
</P>
<P>
In selecting New Orleans as its conference headquarters, CA has
invested significantly in the city's technological infrastructure by
installing more than 600,000 linear feet of fiber optic cable to
network many of the city's hotels to the convention center.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the network also connects an on-site data center in
the convention center with the Computerworld's Islandia corporate
headquarters and the Internet.
</P>
<P>
This year, CA World's impressive list of keynote speakers
include paramount information technology industry leaders, such as
Intel's Chairman Andrew S. Grove, and President and Chief Executive
Officer Craig R, Barret, and former U.S. President Jimmy Carter.
</P>
<P>
With revenue of 5.3 billion U.S. dollars, CA, founded in 1976,
employs more than 14,000 people in 100 countries and regions around
the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
