<HEADLINE> Singapore's Retail Sales Edge Up In May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's retail sales
expanded to 1,818 million Singapore dollars (1,069 million U.S.
dollars) in May 1999, up 5.1 percent over May 1998, the Singapore
Department of Statistics (SDS) said in a press release Monday.
</P>
<P>
Compared to the 1,790 million Singapore dollars (1,053 million
U.S. dollars) in April 1999, retail sales in May 1999 increased by
1.6 percent, SDS said, adding that excluding motor vehicles, it
grew by 7.8 percent following four months of consecutive declines.
</P>
<P>
SDS noted that sales of department stores &AMP; supermarkets and
textiles &AMP; personal effects grew significantly by 17.0 and 14.0
percent respectively, leading gainers in the month.
</P>
<P>
SDS said catering trade in May 1999 fell by 1.7 percent
year-on-year with the total value estimated at 264 million
Singapore dollars (155.3 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Compared with the 250 million Singapore dollars (147 million
U.S. dollars) in the previous month, catering trade picked up by
5.8 percent in May 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
