<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 19 (Xinhua) -- A Russian Emergencies Ministry
transport plane with mobile chemical and radiological laboratories
left here for Yugoslavia Monday, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The labs will be used to test the soil, water and air near
potentially hazardous facilities in Pancevo, Belgrade, Novi Sad
and other settlements of the Balkan country that suffered a 78-day
air campaign by the North Atlantic Treaty Organization.
</P>
<P>
