Yugoslavia Sunday evening, after a break of some three months
following the start of the NATO air strikes.
</P>
<P>
However, the first carriage bound for Yugoslavia will only
reach Novi Sad, about 75 kilometers northwest of Belgrade, rather
than the capital itself, because the railway bridge across the
Danube was destroyed by NATO bombardment.
