<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Conference on Peaceful Use of Outer Space Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan
Monday urged the peaceful exploration of outer space as the United
Nations opened its third conference on peaceful use of outer space.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening session, Annan said, "We must guard
against any misuse of outer space, and we must ensure that the
fruits of technical progress are made available to all people in
all nations."
</P>
<P>
"We recognized early on that a legal regime was needed to
prevent it (from) becoming another arena of military confrontation,
" Annan added, "We cannot take the expanse of space as another
battleground for our earthly conflicts."
</P>
<P>
The first two United Nations conferences on peaceful use of
outer space were held in 1968 and 1982 respectively. The current
one, known as Unispace III, was attended by representatives from
more than 180 member countries and will adopt the Vienna
Declaration to provide international guidelines for the use and
environmental protection of the outer space. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
