<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Shares Close Lower Amidst Retail Selling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange ended lower Monday on retail-led selling.
</P>
<P>
Prices were seen easing back under selling pressure as retail
players took profit from their recent gains.
</P>
<P>
The Composite Index was down 11.35 points or 1.35 percent to
831.77.
</P>
<P>
The broader Emas Index eased 3.11 points to 219.75 while the
Industrial Index slipped 8.97 points to 1,465.13 and Finance Index
slipped 120.48 points to 6,568.67.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers by 458 to 249 while 112 counters
were unchanged and 95 untraded.
</P>
<P>
Daily turnover declined to 715.172 million shares valued at
1.616 billion ringgit (0.425 billion dollars) from 1.26 billion
shares worth 2.944 billion ringgit (0.775 billion dollars) last
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the Main Board declined to 666.208 million shares
valued at 1.482 billion ringgit (0.39 billion dollars) from 1.19
billion shares valued at 2.76 billion ringgit (0.73 billion
dollars) traded on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Second Board turnover dropped to 48.964 million shares worth
134.329 million ringgit (35.35 million dollars) from 69.08 million
shares at 179.68 million ringgit (47.19 million dollars)
previously.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals expanded to 31.877 million shares worth
121.560 million ringgit (31.99 million dollars) from 16.07 million
shares valued at 59.39 million ringgit (15.63 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the Malaysian Exchange of Securities Dealing and Automated
Quotation, the Mesdaq Composite Index (MCI) finished lower by 0.63
of a point to 100. 
</P>
