<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Launches First Rating Agency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Duff &AMP; Phelps Credit Rating (DCR)
Lanka Ltd, the first rating agency in Sri Lanka, said Monday that
it was launched to evaluate local financial institutions and
companies and develop the local corporate debt market
</P>
<P>
"By introducing ratings to the Sri Lankan marketplace, DCR
Lanka will provide local issuers with wider access to capital than
is currently available," DCR Lanka said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement quoted DCR Lanka's chief executive officer Ravi
Abeysuriya as saying, "Credit ratings enhance market transparency,
stability and investor confidence in the market."
</P>
<P>
DCR Lanka is a joint venture between U.S.-based Duff &AMP; Phelps
Credit Rating Co, the International Finance Corporation, the
Central Bank of Sri Lanka and various local commercial banks,
state funds and finance companies.
</P>
<P>
The rating agency will provide independent third-party reviews
and publish quarterly reports on rated companies as well as
industry papers.
</P>
<P>
"DCR Lanka's affiliation with the global rating capabilities of
DCR extends the reach of Sri Lankan issuers to international
investors," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka has been keen to expand its debt market and encourage
local companies to raise cheap finance from overseas. With the
launch of its first rating agency, Sri Lanka is expected to get a
huge boost in debt market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
