<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandan Coffee Exports within World Limit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has been keeping within the
world limits of its quota of coffee exports, a local report said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Uganda exported about four million bags (60 kgs each) of coffee
annually from 1995 to 1998 and expected to export 3.6 million bags
in 1999.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed in a report made by William Naggaga, board
chairman of the Uganda Coffee Development Authority, after
attending a meeting of world coffee producing countries held
between July 6 and 7 in Brasilia, capital of Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Coffee producing countries meeting in Brazil have agreed to
limit coffee exports on the world market at 50 million bags during
the 1999-2000 coffee season, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Coffee is Uganda's biggest foreign exchange earner and
contributes over 55 percent of the hard currency receipt in this
east African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
