<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-19 14:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt's September Referendum to Endorse Mubarak's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Egypt is to hold a referendum on
September 26 to endorse the parliament nomination of President
Hosni Mubarak for a fourth six-year term in office.
</P>
<P>
The country's Middle East News Agency reported on Monday that
Mubarak, 71, has issued a decree calling on all eligible voters to
take part in the referendum that day.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's People's Assembly (lower house) overwhelmingly
nominated Mubarak on June 2 for a further term. He is certain to
win the referendum as he is the sole candidate for the post.
</P>
<P>
Under Egypt's constitution, the nomination of a presidential
candidate must be put forward by one-third of the 454-member
People's Assembly and then be approved by a two-thirds
majority. The nomination is then endorsed in a public referendum.
</P>
<P>
The ruling National Democratic Party led by Mubarak dominates
both the People's Assembly and the Shura Council, the consultative
upper house with no executive or legislative powers.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak, who was vice president under late President Anwar
Sadat, was first elected president in 1981 after Sadat's
assassination by Islamic radicals. He was reelected unopposed in
1987 and 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
