<HEADLINE> Egypt Reaffirms Adherence to One-China Principle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Egypt on Monday reaffirmed adherence
to the principle that there is only one China in the world and
that Taiwan is an inalienable part of China.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with China's Xinhua News Agency, Egyptian
Deputy Prime Minister and Chairman of the Egyptian-Chinese
Friendship Association, Youssef Wali, denounced the separatist
remarks made by Lee Teng-hui, leader of the Taiwanese authorities,
as running counter to the one-China principle.
</P>
<P>
Wali said Lee's remarks also contradict the wishes of the
Taiwanese people for China's reunification.
</P>
<P>
Lee Teng-hui claimed in an interview with a German radio early
this month that the Taiwanese authorities had defined the
relationship across the Taiwan Straits as "state-to-state, or at
least special state-to-state relations."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has condemned Lee's remarks as an utter
exposure of his premeditated intentions to divide the Chinese
territory and sovereignty, and create "two Chinas," "one China,
one Taiwan" or "Taiwan's independence."
</P>
<P>
Wali said Lee's remarks were aimed at intentionally creating
tensions between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits, violating
international norms and jeopardizing the interests of the Chinese
people.
</P>
<P>
He demanded that Lee Teng-hui change his separatist position
and remove all the factors causing tensions between the two sides
of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Wali stressed that the Egyptian people cherish deep feelings
for the Chinese people and side with the Chinese people over
issues closely bound up with the interests of the Chinese people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
