<HEADLINE> Philippines Unveils Millennium Projects, Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government will be
launching several worthwhile projects and activities in line with
the Philippine millennium celebration, the Presidential Palace
said Monday in a news release.
</P>
<P>
According to the release, the millennium celebration begins
from September 23, the start of the 100-day countdown, to December
31, 1999. The whole year of 2000 will be tagged as the new
millennium year.
</P>
<P>
One of the activities is the Department of Tourism's "Milenyo
Pilipino" (Millennium Filipino) program to entice the more than
six million Filipinos residing and working abroad to visit the
country and join in the festivities, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The government has already drafted an executive order which
provides, among others, the creation of a national committee,
composed of relevant government agencies and corporate offices, to
handle the planning and the implementation of the Millennium
Program.
</P>
<P>
The sum of 20 million pesos (500,000 U.S. dollars) will be
allotted as seed money for the various commitments and activities,
including special cultural and entertainment shows and a fireworks
display, said the release.
</P>
<P>
As part of the Milenyo Pilipino Festival, which will start on
December 1, the best of Philippine products, culture, heritage and
tourism will be showcased along Manila's Roxas Boulevard.
</P>
<P>
The boulevard will be designed based on the millennial theme.
It will have food booths, trade fair and such attractions as
replicas of the country's famous Banaue Rice Terraces, Vigan
Heritage Village, and Mayon Volcano. 
</P>
</TEXT>
