Honorary presidents of the preparatory committee were Tung Chee
Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, Jiang Enzhu, director of the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong
Branch, Ma Yuzhen, commissioner of the Foreign Ministry in Hong
Kong, and Xiong Ziren, commander of the People's Liberation Army
Hong Kong Garrison.
</P>
<P>
The preparatory committee has a 120-member presidium composed
of social celebrities, as well as 15 advisors including
Administrative Secretary Anson Chan.
</P>
<P>
It was decided at the meeting that a grand evening party would
be held at the Hong Kong Coliseum on October 2. A number of well-
known actors and actresses of Hong Kong as well as some high-level
artistic troupes from the mainland will participate in the
performance. Sports contests will also be held during the
celebrations.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the launching ceremony, Jiang Enzhu said China has
scored enormous achievements in economic growth and social
progress since the People's Republic of China was founded 50 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
The reform and opening program over the past two decades has
witnessed even more remarkable achievements, which enable the
country to become relatively prosperous and strong, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the practice of the "one country, two systems"
principle had got a very sound beginning in Hong Kong over the
past two years.
</P>
<P>
The success of the "one country, two systems" principle offers
an experience to the smooth return of Macao to China, and brings a
far-reaching impact on Taiwan at the same time, he noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
