<HEADLINE> Guangdong, HK, Macao Police to Jointly Curb Human Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Police authorities in south China's
Guangdong Province, Hong Kong and Macao reached an agreement today
to jointly launch an exercise against the smuggling of human
beings this October near Macao's neighboring city of Zhuhai.
</P>
<P>
This campaign, the first concerted effort by the three police
jurisdictions, aims to combat illegal immigration and crossing-
border crimes, and to ensure a smooth handover of Macao to the
motherland in December, it was announced after a three-party
meeting in Zhuhai today.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 police boats and some 600 border policemen and
maritime policemen from the three places will be involved in the
exercise on October 8 near Zhuhai's Jiuzhou Port. The participants
will stage a procession of police patrol boats and various law-
enforcement exercises.
</P>
<P>
"This is a demonstration of our common determination to
safeguard the handover of Macao," said Lin Jieyuan, chief of the
border police bureau under the Guangdong Department of Public
Security. "We also hope to cooperate more closely in dealing with
maritime accidents."  
</P>
</TEXT>
