<HEADLINE> Pro-Israeli Militiaman Killed in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 19 (Xinhua) -- A member of the pro-Israeli South
Lebanon Army (SLA) was killed Monday during Lebanese guerrillas'
attack, security sources said.
</P>
<P>
The militiaman was killed by a roadside bomb on the road
between Kfar Houna and Rihan in the eastern sector of the Israeli
occupied border zone in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, claimed
responsibility for the attack. It said in a statement that its
fighters detonated a bomb on a group of SLA militiamen at the
Kfar Houna crossing, causing several casualties.
</P>
<P>
In Jerusalem, Israeli army confirmed the attack and the death
of the militiaman.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon
in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from
Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting to oust Israeli forces and its proxy
SLA out of the country. 
</P>
