<HEADLINE> Fund Established in Beijing to Develop Women's  Football </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Women's Federation
established a special fund affiliated with the China Women's
Development Foundation in Beijing today to support the development
of women's football in China.
</P>
<P>
The "China Woman Football Development Fund" received 10 million
yuan (about 1.2 million U.S. dollars) today from the Prosperity
Share Holding Co. Ltd., the first enterprise to donate to the fund.
</P>
<P>
The fund will be used to improve the living and training
conditions of the Chinese women's football team, and expand
domestic and international cooperation and exchanges in women's
football.
</P>
<P>
The China Women's Development Foundation will issue regulations
on the use of the football fund, and will establish a management
committee composed of large donors, renowned public figures,
experts and scholars, and outstanding athletes, coaches, and
sports judges.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Women's Development Foundation has opened a
hotline seeking donations to the fund, and is already receiving
donations from all walks of life.
</P>
<P>
Women's football has gone through several periods of difficulty
since it was developed in China more than a decade ago, said Ma
Yuan'an, coach of the national women's football team, which placed
second at the recent Women's Football Third World Cup.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the lack of financial support has become a
major factor hindering the development of the sport in China, and
he said he hopes this new fund will help promote the game.
</P>
<P>
The donation hotline for the China Women's Football Development
Fund is: (010)65242524. 
</P>
</TEXT>
