<HEADLINE> State Flood-Relief Materials Arrive in Hunan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The first batch of flood-relief
materials from the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters (SFCDRH) arrived today in central China's Hunan
Province, a forefront of the flood-control campaign along the
Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The SFCDRH has allocated 500,000 square meters of plastic and
20,000 life jackets to Hunan, which has entered a critical phase
of its flood-control efforts.
</P>
<P>
Water levels in three major rivers in Hunan have surged above
the warning level, and in some places are above the danger level.
</P>
<P>
Floods on the Yangtze and torrential rains in the province are
expected to raise the water level in Dongting Lake to about 35.5
meters, the second highest since the founding of the People's
Republic of China in 1949, according to local flood-control
officials.
</P>
<P>
Devastating flooding along the Yangtze River and in northeast
China provinces killed more than 3,000 people last year and
resulted in economic losses of 264.2 billion yuan.  
</P>
