<HEADLINE> China Places 6 Maritime Courts into Judicial, Administrative System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- China recently put six maritime
courts in Shanghai, Wuhan, Guangzhou, Dalian, Qingdao, and Tianjin
into the judicial and administrative system.
</P>
<P>
The move put an end to local transport departments'
jurisdiction over the courts.
</P>
<P>
According to an official with the Ministry of Communications,
China began establishing independent maritime courts in 1984.
</P>
<P>
Besides the above-mentioned courts, there are four more
maritime courts in Xiamen, Ningbo, Haikou, and Beihai that have
already been placed in the judicial and administrative system.
</P>
<P>
These ten courts, which locate along China's long coastline,
form a complete maritime judicial and administrative system.By the
end of last year, 26,700 cases had been handled by the courts.
</P>
