<HEADLINE> Guilin Boosts Tourism Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Guilin, the famous tourist
destination in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, has
taken vigorous steps this year to develop new scenic spots, and
has so far completed 17 new tourism projects.
</P>
<P>
The city, renowned for its unique hill formations and rivers,
hosts millions of tourists annually from both home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Guilin, with ten counties under its jurisdiction, boasts not
only splendid natural scenery, but also many historical and
cultural sites.
</P>
<P>
To develop more areas for tourism, the city has constructed and
developed a large number of scenic sites this year, including
renovating an ancient canal, an ancient town, and terraced fields,
a fishing village and temples.
</P>
<P>
A local source said that construction of the new scenic spots
will help the city develop multiple tourist attractions focusing
on natural scenery, folk customs, historical and cultural relics,
and sites for ecological forest tours.  
</P>
