<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Index 1.9 Percent Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The key indicator of share
prices on the Karachi Stock Exchange (KSE) closed 1.9 percent
higher Monday amid optimism that tension at Kargil has ended.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 share price index rose 21.89 points to 1156.67
points from Friday's 1134.78 points.
</P>
<P>
"The market was positive due to quietness at the Kargil front
where the Mujahideen have vacated as scheduled," said Shakeel
Anwar Kamal, a dealer with Prudential Securities Pvt. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
He said this positive development encouraged investors to
purchase blue chip stocks especially petroleum shares because
newspapers reported that the government would increase petroleum
prices by 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
The volume on Monday stood at 123.556 million shares against
Friday's 109.858 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 136 active issues, gainers beat losers 79 to 32 with
25 unchanged. 
