<HEADLINE> Canadian Municipalities Funded to Attract Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- As many as 68 Canadian
municipalities are receiving 1.6 million Canadian dollars (1.09
million U.S. dollars) in aid to attract foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Canadian International Trade Minister Sergio Marchi said
Sunday that the money is the first disbursement from the Program
for Export Market Development-Investment (PEMD-I), the annual
budget of which is 5 million Canadian dollars (about 340 million U.
S. dollars).
</P>
