<HEADLINE> U.S. Embassy Closed in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The Untied States closed its
embassy in Maputo, Mozambique Monday morning due to security
reasons.
</P>
<P>
Harriet Mcguire, cultural and press official at the embassy,
said the move is to prevent accidents and casualties.
</P>
<P>
For the past few weeks, the United States' foreign agencies
including the embassy in Mozambique, have been the targets of
threat, therefore she said the temporary closure of the embassy is
a wise move.
</P>
<P>
The United States also closed its consulate, cultural section,
library and other offices in Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
U.S. embassy in Mozambique has reinforced its security
precautions following the bombing of embassies in Tanzania and
Kenya last August. In the past month, the United States has
surrounded its embassy with concrete frusta as high as one meter
without the approval of the Maputo authorities, which caused the
dissatisfaction of both Maputo citizens and city officials.
</P>
