state since the country's independence in 1960.
</P>
<P>
Though the number of French nationals living in Nigeria has
been falling for the past five years, France remains a big
importer of Nigeria's oil.
</P>
<P>
Recently, France has helped underwrite the cost of launching
French classes in the West African English-speaking country where
more than one million students are studying the French language in
various institutions. 
