<HEADLINE> Singapore to Host Major ASEAN Meetings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Singapore will host three major
meetings of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN)
from July 23 to 28, the Singapore Foreign Ministry said Monday in
a statement.
</P>
<P>
The 32nd ASEAN Ministerial Meeting (AMM) and the 6th ASEAN
Regional Forum (ARF) will be held on July 23-24 and July 26
respectively, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The other meeting is the annual Post Ministerial Conferences
(PMC) with ASEAN's dialogue partners on July 27-28.
</P>
<P>
At the AMM, foreign ministers from all ten member countries of
ASEAN including Cambodia will review ASEAN's activities and
external relations over the past year and lay down policy
guidelines for the coming year, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
At the ARF on July 26, the ministers are expected to have
candid and free-flowing discussions on regional and international
security issues.
</P>
<P>
At the PMC to be held on July 27-28, the ministers will
exchange views with their counterparts from the ten dialogue
partner countries.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN foreign ministers will also hold separate discussions
with each dialogue partner and Singapore will chair the
discussions with the Republic of Korea and with India, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand, Vietnam and Cambodia. Singapore,
which currently holds the chairmanship of ASEAN, will preside over
these meetings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
