<DOCNO> XIE19990719.0133 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Economy Surges 11.9 Percent (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The tourism sector in Beijing enjoyed an upturn with the
gradual economic recovery of the southeast Asian countries.
Arrivals by overseas tourists increased by 11.4 percent to 1.05
million during the first six months.
</P>
<P>
A total of 309 overseas-funded projects were approved during
the period, involving 1.59 billion US dollars in contractual
investment, down 6.1 percent and 24.3 percent from the same 1998
period, respectively.
</P>
<P>
But the city used 3.7 percent more of overseas capital during
the period, which totaled 1.36 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The overseas trade volume expanded by 13.7 percent to 15.57
billion US dollars worth. Export declined by 10.1 percent to 4.41
billion US dollars worth, while import surged by 27 percent to 11.
16 billion US dollars worth.
</P>
<P>
Inflation continued to remain at a low level, with the consumer
price index and retail price index edging up 2.7 percent and 0.7
percent on the yearly basis, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
