<HEADLINE> Share Prices End Lower on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed lower on
Singapore Stock Market Monday with the benchmark Straits Times
Index (STI) losing 12.88 points to close at 2,121.34.
</P>
<P>
The volume decreased to 497.59 million shares valued at 593.95
million Singapore dollars (about 349.38 million U.S. dollars).
Losers led gainers by 240 to 106 with 100 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
AFP was the most heavily traded stock with a turnover of 45.73
million shares. It was followed by GoldenAg that had 45.68 million
units done. Hutung was the next with 34.84 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SIA led the gainers of the day gaining 110 cents to close at
15.50 Singapore dollars. SIA 200 climbed up 90 cents to finish at
15.30 Singapore dollars. SIA DBS w0 edged up 80 cents to end at
9.10 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH 100 headed the descent losing 110 cents to
finish at 33.90 Singapore dollars. OCBC F sank 60 cents to close
at 14.50 Singapore dollars. OCBC retreated 50 cents to end at
12.30 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
SIA local shares rose 1.10 Singapore dollars after it announced
plans on Friday to merge its local and foreign shares and buy back
shares worth up to one billion Singapore dollars (about 588.24
million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
