<HEADLINE> Tremor Shakes Sumba Strait, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.7 on the
Richter scale shook Sumba Strait and western part of Flores
Island, Indonesia, on Monday at 13:00 local time (05:00 GMT).
</P>
<P>
The epicentrum of the quake was at the seabed in Sumba Strait,
Antara News Agency reported, adding that there was no immediate
reports about material losses and casualties. 
