<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2,400-Year-Old Tombs Found in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archaeologists have
found four tombs dating back to the Warring States Period (475 B.C.
-221 B.C.) in Xinyang City in Henan Province, central China.
</P>
<P>
Unearthed from the tombs were more than 20 pieces of pottery
utensils and a dozen items of bamboo and lacquerware, in addition
to some dried grain and fruit.
</P>
<P>
The experts said that the discovery will provide valuable clues
for the study of ancient culture, agriculture and handicrafts in
the area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
