<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Culture Park to Mark Confucius' Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 19 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province will
build a culture park to mark the 2,550th anniversary of the birth
of Confucius, the leading scholar in ancient China, according to
local officials.
</P>
<P>
The park, to cost 200 million yuan, will be located in Rushan
City and cover an area of four ha, with 20,000 sq m of buildings.
</P>
<P>
Confucius (551 B.C.-479 B.C.) is regarded not only as the
founder of Confucianism and a great thinker and educator in
ancient China, but also as one of the greatest scholars in the
world.
</P>
<P>
In the park will be rocks on which the sage's 2,860 quotations
regarded as the basic elements of Confucianism will be engraved.
Confucianism was a theory that had a great impact on the
development of China's feudal society.
</P>
<P>
The park will also feature a pavilion made of stained glass. It
will be engraved with famous quotations from ancient scholars such
as Confucius and Mencius, and contemporary scholars and scientists.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990719.0144 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bankrupt Real Estate Joint Venture Auctioned Off in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Assets of a real estate joint
venture between a Beijing developer and a Hong Kong-based company
has been auctioned off at a price of 398 million yuan (about 48
million U.S. dollars) to pay off creditors.
</P>
<P>
The Xisen Group Co. Ltd from Leling of east China's Shandong
Province, one of the largest debtors of the Beijing L &AMP; D Rose
Garden Villa Co. Ltd, bought the famous "Rose Garden Villa"
residential houses at the auction held over the weekend to
minimize its losses.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing L &AMP; D Rose Garden Villa Co. Ltd was formerly the
Beijing Feida Rose Garden Villa Co. Ltd, a joint venture between
Beijing Changping County Real Estate Development Corp. and the
Hong Kong-based China Feida Real Estate Limited with a registered
capital of 15 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Located in the north suburbs of Beijing, the "Rose Garden Villa
" project, had planned to build more than 800 villas on nearly 500,
000 sq. km of land and a total of 186 villas of American, Japanese
and European styles were completed.
</P>
<P>
The ownership of the shares of the Beijing L &AMP; D Rose Garden
Villa Co. Ltd, the developer of the Rose Villa Project, has
changed several times in recent years while the operation and
management were steadily deteriorating, resulting in heavy
deficits.
</P>
<P>
In September 1997, the court declared that the company must
file for bankruptcy and 105 creditors have registered with total
debt rights worth one billion yuan. The majority are from Hong
Kong, with a few foreigners.
</P>
<P>
The company was then liquidated and the Rose Villa project was
evaluated to be worth 600 million yuan. The Beijing No.1
Intermediate People's Court ruled in June the project be auctioned
off to pay off some of the creditors.
</P>
<P>
The court has also ruled that house buyers who have made a
whole or partial payment could move into the villas as normal or
could ask for a refund as a common creditor, in accordance with
the law, and be repaid on a proportional basis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
