Mahat stressed Nepal's stand on its "one China" policy when
meeting with a visiting Chinese delegation here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Nepal took the principle of the one China policy from the very
beginning and firmly supports China's stand on Taiwan and Tibet
issues," he said.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said that Nepal's consistent practice is
to stick to the principles on international affairs as well as on
China.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, Nepal maintains that Taiwan and Tibet are the
integrated parts of China.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is a great neighbor of Nepal and the two
countries have no problems on bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
"Our relations have been very cordial," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mahat praised China's great achievements in economic and social
developments scored in recent years.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's experiences in economic development are
valuable and should become an example for other countries,
especially Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
He encouraged more economic and business exchanges between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The delegation of the China Association for International
Friendly Contact arrived here for a six-day visit on July 17.
