year declined 7 percent to their lowest levels since the Justice
Department began tracking the figure in 1973, Attorney General
Janet Reno announced here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The report said preliminary figures released separately by the
Federal Bureau of Investigation have shown that the number of
murders dropped about 8 percent between 1997 and 1998.
</P>
<P>
