<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang Reports Rapid Border Trade Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Border trade between northeast
China's Heilongjiang Province and Russia has continued to increase
steadily, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang's border trade volume totaled 695.4 million US
dollars in the first six months of this year, a surge of 24.7
percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The import and export values reached 309.2 million US dollars
and 386.2 million US dollars, 70.2 percent and 2.7 percent up,
respectively, compared to the January-June period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The major import products during the period included paper pulp,
timber, steel and chemical materials. The export products included
textiles, garments and foodstuffs. 
</P>
