<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas-funded Ventures Expand Business in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Overseas-funded ventures in this
Chinese capital are expanding their business thanks to improving
investment climate and promising market prospects.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics from the Municipal Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation Commission showed that a total of 986 million
US dollars of overseas investment flowed into Beijing during the
January-June period, including 525 million US dollars from
existing overseas-funded ventures.
</P>
<P>
Companies that increased their investment by more than 20
million US dollars include Ericsson Mobile Communications Co. Ltd,
Lucent Technologies and Japan's SMC Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
"It's the fourth year in a row for my firm to increase its
investment since we set up our China branch in Beijing in 1994,"
said Zhao Tong, president of Japan SMC (China) Co. Ltd. "We have
injected nearly 100 million US dollars into the China market so
far, compared to our initial investment of ten million US dollars.
"
</P>
<P>
The foreign partner of a pharmaceuticals company said his
company is mainly attracted by the improved investment climate in
Beijing and the huge market potential.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government has adopted a series of measures and
policies since last year to increase the city's attraction for
overseas investment, including preferential policies to encourage
overseas investment in new, high-tech industries, and regulations
designed to draw more multinationals to set up their regional
headquarters in Beijing and start technological development
centers, according to a municipal trade official.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the total industrial output value of
overseas-funded businesses in Beijing surged 33 percent during the
first five months of this year to 27.875 billion yuan, while the
sales income rose 33.8 percent to 41.94 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
By late June, Beijing had approved a total of 14,390 overseas-
funded ventures, involving 26.86 billion US dollars in contractual
investment. A total of 438 multinationals and world-renowned
enterprises have established branch companies in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
