<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia Reiterates its "One China" Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Foreign Minister Hor
Nam Hong reaffirmed Monday that the Royal Government of Cambodia
has always pursued the "One-China" policy and firmly supported the
principled stance of the Chinese government on resolving the
Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Hor Nam Hong made the remark in a meeting with Chinese
Ambassador to Cambodia Yan tingai Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Cambodian government is giving close attention
to the latest development of the cross-straits relationship.
</P>
<P>
He said that the recent remark made by Lee Teng-hui about the
cross-straits relationship is very dangerous and catastrophical.
It will not only be harmful to the cross-straits relationship, but
also damage the stability of the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Taiwan issue is the internal affairs of China,
so it should be resolved by the Chinese government and its people
independently and with the initiative in their own hands. No
country has the right to interfere, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
