<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Turkish newspapers on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet (National):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem said that Turkey
considers Kosovars as a people with whom Turkey shares a common
history and culture.
</P>
<P>
Cem visited Turkish troops that serve under KFOR in Kosovo and
attended the opening ceremony of the coordination center
established by the Turkish Red Crescent.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet (Freedom):
</P>
<P>
-- Iran claimed that Turkish jets bombarded a military base
close to Piransehir and threatened to reciprocate, causing
tensions in the ties between the two neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Ministry Spokesman Hamid Riza Asefi claimed
that Turkish planes bombed Iran, taking a toll of civilians and
revolutionary guards.
</P>
<P>
Daily News:
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish State Minister Sukru Sina Gerel said Turkey will not
back off from its position on a Cyprus solution, but has left the
door open for a formula that can provide the resumption of talks
without the official recognition of the "Turkish Republic of
Northern Cyprus" as a state.
</P>
<P>
However, Gerel pointed out that providing equality between the
two Cypriot sides is a must. 
</P>
