<HEADLINE> Macao Attracts More Tourists from Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 19 (Xinhua) -- With Macao's upcoming return to the
motherland, more people in the mainland areas of China tend to pay
a visit to the unique place which blends Chinese and Western
styles.
</P>
<P>
Now that many people have growing interest in Macao and want to
know more about the place, some provincial branches of the China
International Travel Service Co. Ltd. in the mainland are
arranging large tourist groups to Macao.
</P>
<P>
On July 17, a total of 677 tourists from southwest China's
Guizhou Province arrived in Macao. They made the travel by train
first to Guangzhou City which is about two hours' ride to Macao.
</P>
<P>
The Guizhou branch of the travel service began preparations for
the trip one month ago. According to an original plan, the number
of tourists was estimated to be around 570, but as many as 800
people applied to join in. Some people had to stay for a future
trip.
</P>
<P>
On July 21, a 750-member tourist group from east China's
Zhejiang Province will also come to Macao. Likewise, the tourists
will go to Guangzhou by train first.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the Macao branch of the travel service said that
many other provincial branches in the mainland are also
considering organizing large tourist groups to Macao. 
