shot to the back at a political function on Saturday night
celebrating the 20th anniversary of the ruling Human Rights
Protection Party.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that a man was seen with a rifle on his
shoulder running away after the shooting.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, there is no confirmation about the motivation for
the murder, and the suspect is still at large.
</P>
<P>
Upon hearing the killing of Levaula, who took his law degrees
at Victoria and Auckland universities in New Zealand, New Zealand
acting Minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade Simon Upton said in a
statement that the death means New Zealand has lost a "great
friend."
</P>
<P>
"The death, in such tragic circumstances, is a matter of great
loss to Samoa," he added. 
</P>
