<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-19 06:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Protests Turkish Bombing on Iranian Villages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian Foreign Ministry on
Sunday night summoned Turkish Charge d'Affairs to Tehran Kut
Sezgin, strongly protesting against Turkish bombardment on Iranian
border villages earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian ministry condemned the aggression and violation of
Iranian airspace by Turkish warplanes, saying Iran reserves the
right to take any actions against the aggression and violation,
the Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Iran underlined that the Turkish government should shoulder
the consequences of the aggression, offer an official apology to
Iran, pay compensations to Iran and avoid the repetition of such
incidents in the future.
</P>
<P>
Governor General of Iran's northwestern West Azarbaijan
province Mahmoud Mirlowhi announced that five people were killed
and 10 others injured in the raid early Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
Mirlowhi said that four Turkish warplanes raided a military
outpost on Iran-Iraq border and tribal tents in a region five
kilometers deep in the Iranian territory.
</P>
<P>
In the first reaction, Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman
Hamid Reza Asefi on Sunday strongly condemned the raid and said
that the attack was "unprovoked and unexplainable."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the headquarters of Iran's armed forces Sunday
night also severely denounced the violation of Iranian airspace
by Turkish warplanes and called it as a flagrant violation of the
international law and against the good neighborly relations .
</P>
<P>
Issuing a statement, the headquarters said that Iran reserves
the right to react in accordance with the international laws
and regulations and considers Turkey as responsible for any
consequences to the event.
</P>
<P>
It also called on international bodies to look into the
accident and condemn the aggressive act, expressing hope that
the Turkish government should not be affected by "the Israeli
insinuations and avoid from any action which could harm the
good neighborly relations and threaten the regional calm and
security." 
</P>
</TEXT>
