<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pudong Reports High Foreign Trade Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong New Area, an emerging
financial and trade zone in this east China metropolis, did 6.73
billion U.S. dollars-worth of foreign trade in the first half of
this year, an increase of 36.7 percent over the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the local Customs department indicate
that the area exported 2.87 billion U.S. dollars-worth of
commodities during the January-June period, up 31 percent, while
importing 3.86 billion U.S. dollars-worth of goods, up 41 percent.
</P>
<P>
Local trade experts attributed the high growth mainly to
increases in the external trade of overseas-funded enterprises and
high-tech products.
</P>
<P>
According to the Shanghai Customs, more than half of the
exports and imports were accomplished by the area's 2,000-odd
overseas-funded enterprises, compared with 15 percent in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Technology-intensive goods, such as computers and machinery,
made up 50 percent of the total exports, while exports of labor-
and resource-intensive products kept on declining.
</P>
<P>
The United States, Japan and Germany are the biggest trading
partners of the area in terms of trade volume.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
