<HEADLINE> Turkey Seizes Over 100 Kilograms of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 19 (xinhua) -- Turkish gendarme soldiers have
seized 101.7 kilograms of pure heroin in an anti-drug operation
in eastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off, the Turkish gendarme soldiers Sunday
searched a house at Guroluk village in Baskale town of Van
province bordering Iran and found the heroin, the local daily
Hurriyet (Freedom) reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ten suspected smugglers including one Iranian were arrested
for alleged involvement in the case, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Turkish police conducted 2,928 operations against
drug-trafficking last year and seized over 10 tons of drugs,
including 5.3 tons of hashish and 3.8 tons of heroin.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs from the border area of
Afghanistan and Pakistan to Europe. 
</P>
