<HEADLINE> Hovercraft Route to Open on Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 19 (Xinhua) -- A hovercraft route between Longmen
Pass and Hukou Waterfall, a section of the Yellow River on the
borders of Shaanxi and Shanxi provinces, has opened on a trial
basis, and is expected to go into service in August or September.
</P>
<P>
The 60-km route takes two hours to traverse.
</P>
<P>
Two hovercraft, valued at 2.8 million yuan (330,000 US dollars),
shuttle between the two places, each carrying 40 passengers at a
time.
</P>
<P>
The route is flanked by scenic landscapes and lush green
mountains including Shaanxi's Hancheng City, a state-listed
historical and cultural city.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the water route will be extended downstream
to Sanmenxia City in central China via Tongguan City in Shaanxi in
the near future.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a statue and a museum in memory of Dayu, the reputed
founder of the Xia Dynasty (21 Century B.C.-16 Century B.C.), who
led the people in their efforts to control floodwaters in ancient
China, will be built in Longmen.  
</P>
</TEXT>
