<HEADLINE> Shooting Completed on Chinese Cartoon "Baby Kitten" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The shooting of a 90-minute
cartoon film, "Baby Kitten", produced jointly by China Central
Television (CCTV) and the Beijing Science and Education Film
Studio, has been completed, and it will soon be screened in
cinemas all over the country.
</P>
<P>
China has produced only a few lengthy cartoon films. "Facing
the challenge of foreign cartoon films and the demand from
youngsters and children in our country, the cartoonists are
working hard to produce more high-quality cartoon films and TV
series nowadays," said an official from China's movie industry.
</P>
<P>
"Baby Kitten" tells the story of how a little cat finds its way
back home. It underlines the importance of developing the
abilities of youngsters and children, such as the ability to
engage in independent thinking, problem solving and communication.
</P>
<P>
"The cartoon's message is particularly significant in this era
of the one-child family in China," the official said.
</P>
<P>
The one-child policy was adopted in the 1970s in order to hold
down the country's population growth.
</P>
<P>
"Baby Kitten" was remade from a 10-episode TV cartoon series "
Adventures of a Baby". The 90-minute cartoon film represents a
marked improvement in terms of action, language, pictures and
music compared to the TV series. 
</P>
</TEXT>
