<HEADLINE> China's 1st Marine Technology Trade Center Set up in Qingdao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 19 (Xinhua) -- China's first marine technology
market, the Qingdao Marine Technology Trade Center, has opened in
this coastal city in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The center, aiming to become a national one eventually, will
focus on the trading of marine development technologies, exchange
of information concerning marine industries, and technical
services,
</P>
<P>
Jiang Huashan, director of the Qingdao Municipal Commission for
Science and Technology, referred to the move as part of the city's
efforts to become a marine industry center.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao is home to 25 marine research institutes, which employ
more than 5,000 professionals, or 40 percent of the country's
total marine research personnel.
</P>
<P>
China, facing the problems of a growing population and a
shortage of onshore resources, has stepped up efforts to develop
its sea areas. Many coastal provinces, such as Shandong, Zhejiang,
Fujian and Guangdong, are working to turn their marine economy
into a major economic growth area in the years to come.  
</P>
