<HEADLINE> Myanmar Commemorates Martyrs' Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar held a state ceremony here
Monday to pay respects to fallen heroes who sacrificed their lives
in the struggle for the country's independence in 1947.
</P>
<P>
The 52nd anniversary Myanmar Martyrs' Day ceremony, which took
place at the Martyrs' Mausoleum in commemoration of the passing
away of the late National Independence Hero General Aung San and
eight others, was attended by Minister of Culture U Win Sein on
behalf of Chairman of the Myanmar State Peace and Development
Council Senior General Than Shwe.
</P>
<P>
The late General's bereaved daughter Aung San Suu Kyi, who is
General Secretary of the opposition National League for Democracy,
also took part in the ceremony as a martyr's family status, laying
wreaths and baskets of flower at the tombs.
</P>
<P>
52 years ago, on July 19, 1947, the late General, along with
his eight Councilor Members, was assassinated at the then
Secretariat Office (now Office of the Ministers) in Yangon six
months before Myanmar regained independence from British
colonialists on January 4, 1948. 
</P>
