</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE) will maintain its
ban on import of British beef despite the European Commission's
decision to allow Britain U.K. to export cattle meat.
</P>
<P>
The issue of lifting the ban on British beef must be taken up
by the UAE's General Secretariat of Municipalities (GSM), the Gulf
News daily on Sunday quoted Dubai Municipality sources as saying.
(UAE-Beef-Ban)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- For the first time in 17 years, Indian annual rate
of inflation fell to 1.83 percent for the week ended July 3, due
mainly to a steady decline in vegetable prices.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics published here on Sunday showed that the
index for vegetables during the week was at 430.6 as against 699.1
in the correspondent period of last year. (India-Inflation-Down)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HARARE -- The International Monetary Fund (IMF) has finally
agreed to disburse 200 million U.S. dollars to Zimbabwe over the
next 14 months starting from two weeks' time under a new balance
of payments support agreement, The Sunday Mail reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
This puts an end to almost two years of an agonizing wait by
Zimbabwe to receive the much needed balance of payments support
which was expected to prop up the country's ailing economy,
strengthen the local currency as well as unlock over 300 million U.
S. dollars support from other international donors. (Zimbabwe-IMF
Fund) 
</P>
