<HEADLINE> Qingdao Bonded Zone Attracts Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The bonded zone in this coastal
city in east China's Shandong Province is attracting an increasing
number of both domestic and overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
So far, the zone has approved 1,234 projects, including 620
funded by overseas investors, with total investments worth 1.097
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Given approval by China's State Council in November 1992, the
bonded zone, covering 2.5 sq km, is empowered to handle imports
and exports, export-oriented processing and duty-free warehousing.
</P>
<P>
Sun Wenlong, deputy director of the zone's administration
committee, said that the zone operates according to international
practices, with the emphasis on creating a favorable business
environment.
</P>
<P>
The Regulations on the Administration of the Qingdao Bonded
Zone were enacted by the standing committee of the Shandong
Provincial People's Congress in 1994, to guarantee the sound
development of the zone.
</P>
<P>
According to Sun, the zone has now established a complete
industrial framework of export-oriented processing, importing and
exporting, re-exporting and warehousing.
</P>
<P>
Investors from some 40 countries and regions have set up
subsidiaries in the zone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
