<DOCNO> XIE19990719.0230 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Coffee Export Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam exported 217,000 tones of
coffee beans in the first six months of this year, an increase
10.2 percent over the same period last year, according to a report
of Vietnam's English daily Vietnam News on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The trade earned more than 300 million U.S. dollars, Vietnam's
General Statistics Office said.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's coffee has been exported to more than 50 countries
and territories with the United States, Germany and Italy being
the biggest customers.
</P>
<P>
The country aims to earn more than 500 million U.S. dollars
from exports of more than 400,000 tones of coffee beans this year.
</P>
<P>
Coffee is now Vietnam's second biggest farm export after rice.
The country has in the past five years become one of the world's
top ten exporters. In the 1997-98 crop, Vietnam ranked third after
Brazil and Colombia in terms of coffee export volume.
</P>
<P>
The world coffee price decreased sharply this year, and
Vietnam's coffee dropped to 1,118 U.S. dollars per tone, the
Vietnam Coffee Corporation said. Coffee prices are now on the rise
but Vietnam still has stockpiles of 50,000 tones of coffee beans
ready for export.
</P>
<P>
More than 300,000 ha in the country are now planted with
coffee, mainly in central highlands and central southern
provinces.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam is striving to expand coffee areas to 400,000 ha with
an expected output of 550,000 tones by 2005, earning 1 billion
U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990719.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gansu's GDP Up in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
generated 30 billion yuan (3.6 billion US dollars) in gross
domestic product in the first half of this year, up eight percent
over last year's same period.
</P>
<P>
The output of summer grain in Gansu is expected to decline by
930,000 tons compared with last year as a result of a 180-day
serious drought. However, both the cash income and expenditure of
local farmers increased in the first six months.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output value of township-run enterprises in
Gansu totaled 29.2 billion yuan at the end of June, a 14-percent
rise. The added value of state-owned and key non-state firms
surged 6.4 percent, to reach 9.3 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
A provincial official attributed the rapid economic growth
mainly to relatively high investment in fixed assets. Gansu
invested 11 billion yuan in fixed assets in the first half of the
year, 3.2 billion yuan more than the figure for the same period of
last year. Investment in infrastructure totaled 5.5 billion yuan,
accounting for half of the total investment in fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
Gansu's import and export value had declined to 145 million U.S.
dollars by the end of May, a drop of 27 percent compared with last
year's same period.
</P>
<P>
The disposable income of urban residents per capita at the end
of June averaged 2,255 yuan, up 13 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
