<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Highlights Development of Rural Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese economists have pointed
out that stimulating the rural market is becoming increasingly
crucial to the country's economic growth in light of the
sluggishness of the urban market.
</P>
<P>
China has a rural population of 900 million, and each one-yuan-
worth of consumption will increase the demand of related
industrial and agricultural means of production by some 140
percent, according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Figures show that 58 percent of the rural population lives on
the level of only having sufficient food and clothing, while the
proportion at the well-off level is increasing.
</P>
<P>
Surveys show that the purchasing power of the well-off farmers
is comparatively high, and so the rural market has great
consumption potential.
</P>
<P>
China stepped up the development of the rural market in 1996,
and since then it has grown more active. In some cities and
provinces, the growth rate of the sales volume in rural areas has
exceeded that of the urban market.
</P>
<P>
From January to May this year, the total retail sales of the
rural market grew 6.3 percent on a year-on-year basis, only 0.6
percentage points lower than urban sales.
</P>
<P>
Guo Shouzhong, a market analyst with the State Administration
of Internal Trade (SAIT), said that the main obstacle to the
stimulation of the rural market is the low growth of farmers' cash
income.
</P>
<P>
"Only by increasing the amount of cash in farmers' pockets can
the potential of the rural market be fully tapped," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He also urged domestic enterprises to develop new products
which meet the demands of the rural population, and halt the
practice of selling over-supplied goods in the rural market.
</P>
<P>
The SAIT and related government departments are making enhanced
efforts to expand sales outlets in rural areas by cultivating
chain stores, agencies, franchises and other new business formats.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990719.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
