<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- AMP, Australia's largest life
insurance company, has just launched a big housing project in this,
China's leading industrial and commercial city.
</P>
<P>
AMP President George Trumbull said the move is part of the
company's massive program to increase investment in China.
</P>
<P>
According to Trumbull, the housing project will cost a total of
60 million U.S. dollars and will act as a springboard for the
insurer to enter the real estate markets in other large Chinese
cities.
</P>
<P>
"China has a dozen cities each with a population of at least
one million, and housing is a problem for many of them," Trumbull
said.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project is to construct 20 buildings
containing 800 flats in four years in the Pudong New Area, an
emerging financial and trade zone in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
AMP has put 600 million U.S. dollars-worth of investment into
the telecommunications and transportation sectors in Beijing,
Nanjing, Dalian, Xiamen and several other Chinese cities since it
entered China in 1997. 
