Government's commitment to stick to its "one China" policy.
</P>
<P>
-- The Subcommittee for Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan Compatriots
and Overseas Chinese of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) issued a
statement yesterday severely condemning Lee Teng-hui's separatist
remarks.
</P>
<P>
Lee's separatist remarks have posed a great threat to cross-
Straits relations and harmed the stability of cross-Straits
relations, in disregard of the desire of all Chinese in the world
to seek peaceful reunification, according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
 Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- Lee Teng-hui is taking a very dangerous step by redefining
cross-Straits relations as "state-to-state", which reveals his
intention to separate Taiwan from China, according to a commentary
from Xinhua News Agency yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The article stressed that the "one China" principle is the
foundation and prerequisite for the development of cross-Straits
relations and the reunification of the motherland.
</P>
