New Zealand will host the informal leadership meeting of APEC
members this September, and Chinese President Jiang Zemin will pay
a state visit to New Zealand, adding that the visit will be a
major event in Sino-New Zealand ties and have a far-reaching
impact upon the stable development of bilateral relations since it
will be the first state visit to that country by a Chinese
President.
</P>
