<HEADLINE> Five Killed in Train Accident in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Five people were instantly killed
after being hit by an express train at the Warung Contong crossing
near Bandung, capital of Indonesia's West Java province, on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The train ran over and dragged the five as far as more than 10
meters after the crossing attendant opened the gate not knowing
that the Bandung-bound train would pass, Eyewitnesses said, quoted
by the Antara News Agency on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The attendant had earlier closed the gate as a train heading
for Jakarta from Bandung was passing.
</P>
<P>
The attendant was escaped shortly after the accident, the
report said. 
</P>
