<HEADLINE> Major Smuggling Case Cracked in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Local police have uncovered a major
smuggling case at the Gongbei Customs in south China's Guangdong
Province, seizing 600 boxes of computer and motor vehicle parts.
</P>
<P>
The case involved two million yuan-worth of cargo smuggled by
ship from Hong Kong to Guangdong. The illegal goods included spare
parts for automobiles, motorcycles and computers, as well as 110,
000 pirated VCDs.
</P>
<P>
In view of the rampant smuggling of vehicle parts by sea this
year, customs officers at Gongbei have increased their offshore
patrols and tightened inspections at key areas. 
