<HEADLINE> De Beers Displaying Rare Diamond Rings In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- De Beers, the world's famous
diamond supplier, is showing a collection of rare diamond rings in
Shanghai, as the first stop in a China tour from July 16 to August
1.
</P>
<P>
On display are 39 engagement and wedding rings used by some
prominent people over the past 600 years. One was the engagement
ring of Mary of Burgundy who became engaged to Maximilian of
Austria in 1477 and the world's first recorded engagement ring.
</P>
<P>
Another was the wedding ring of Elizabeth Barrett, the wife of
the poet Robert Browning, who refers the ring in a poem.
</P>
<P>
The show will go on to the Chinese capital and to Guangzhou,
the capital of Guangdong Province.  
</P>
