<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suzhou Reports High Export Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, July 19 (Xinhua) -- This city in east China's Jiangsu
Province, famous for its picturesque gardens, has reported a 25.4
percent growth in exports for the first half of this year,
compared to the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the city exported more than 2.85 billion U.
S. dollars-worth of commodities during the January-June period.
</P>
<P>
The city's trade with Asian countries has shown visible signs
of recovery, with exports to the Republic of Korea alone surging
122.6 percent during that time.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Europe and the United States both continued to
increase -- by 20.7 percent and 41.9 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Of the exports, 54.5 percent are mechanical and electrical
products.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded enterprises are playing a major role in
boosting Suzhou's exterior trade. So far, the city has approved 6,
963 overseas-funded businesses, 4,369 of which are now operational
and sell the majority of their products abroad.  
</P>
</TEXT>
