<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian to Exhibit World's Biggest Embroidered Buddha </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The biggest embroidered portrait of
Buddha in the world will be the highlight of the Tibetan Folk Art
Festival to be held in this scenic coastal city in northeast China
's Liaoning Province from August 5 to 15.
</P>
<P>
The patch of colored satin carrying the portrait measures 45 m
by 35 m and weighs 3.5 tons. It will be the third time for this
work of art to be exhibited after being displayed in the Tibet
Autonomous Region and Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The festival will feature various arts crafts works from Tibet,
including hand-made carpets, clothing, tents, masks, and articles
used in Tibetan religious ceremonies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
