<HEADLINE> Belgium Beat Switzerland in Davis Cup 1/4 Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Xavier Malisse came from one set
down to lift hosts Belgium to a 3-2 victory over Switzerland and a
semi-final berth in this year's Davis Cup World Group tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian national titlist pulled together after dropping the
opening set of the first reverse singles to beat Roger Federer 4-6,
6-3, 7-5 and 7-6 (7-5).
</P>
<P>
The hosts took an early lead after winning Friday's opening
singles. Malisse downed Lorenzo Manta in straight sets while
Christophe van Garsse went the complete distance before clinching
his match 7-6 (7-4), 3-6, 1-6, 7-5 and 6-1 over Federer.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, the Belgian duo of Malisse and last year's Davis
Cup veteran Filip Dewulf went down to Marc Rosset and Manta in the
doubles match, 6-2, 1-6, 6-7 and 5-7.
</P>
<P>
Van Garsse dropped the remaining singles match of Sunday as he
retired after losing the opening set 6-7 to Manta.
</P>
<P>
Belgium next meets France in late September in a place yet to
be announced. 
</P>
</TEXT>
