<HEADLINE> British Open Golf Goes into Play-off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The British Open golf championship,
which is being held in Carnoustie, Scotland has gone into a three-
way play-off with Scotland's Paul Lawrie, Justin Leonard of the
United States and France's Jean Van de Velde.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Van de Velde tossed away a three-stroke lead at the
final hole in one of the most dramatic finishes in the
championship's history on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Lawrie, who carded a final round 67, and Leonard, 72, waiting
to see what happened, Van de Velde chipped out of the sand and
then rolled in a 4-foot putt to join the duo in a play-off.
</P>
</TEXT>
