<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lawrie Wins British Open After Play-off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Paul Lawrie of Scotland held off
French qualifier Jean Van de Velde and 1997 champion Justin
Leonard in a four hole play-off to win the British Open golf
championship in Carnoustie, Scotland on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old from Aberdeen birdied the third play-off hole --
the 17th - and then kept his nerve with a superb approach on the
last to make another birdie three as his rivals faltered.
</P>
<P>
The trio had finished the regulation 72 holes on six-over-par
290.
</P>
<P>
Lawrie had earlier fired a four-under par 67, the best round of
the day, to close a seven-shot gap on overnight leader Van de
Velde.
</P>
<P>
The Frenchman blew a three-shot cushion on the last hole,
taking a triple bogey seven when a six would have given him the
title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
